# 5-DOF Robotic Arm Assembly and Operating Guide


# Materials Required

## Electronics

| Quantity | Component                                   |
| -------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | Arduino Uno                                 |
| 1        | PCA9685 Servo Driver Module (or equivalent) |
| 1        | 5V 2A Power Supply                          |
| 3        | MG996R Servo Motors (Base, Shoulder, Elbow) |
| 2        | MG90 Servo Motors (Wrist, Gripper)          |
| 1        | USB Cable for Arduino                       |
| Several  | Male-to-Female Jumper Wires                 |


# Step 1: Print All 3D Parts

After printing all 3D parts, assemble the robotic arm from the base upward:

Recommended print settings:

* Material: PLA
* Layer Height: 0.20 mm
* Infill: 20% to 30%
* Supports: As required
* Wall Count: 3

After printing:

1. Remove all support material.
2. Clean mounting holes.
3. Test fit all parts before assembly.

Base Joint
Install an MG996R servo into the base mount.
Secure it with screws.
Attach the base platform to the servo horn.

Shoulder Joint
Install an MG996R servo into the shoulder bracket.
Attach the upper arm link to the servo horn.

Elbow Joint
Install an MG996R servo into the elbow mount.
Attach the forearm link to the servo horn.

Wrist Joint
Install an MG90 servo into the wrist mount.
Attach the wrist assembly to the servo horn.

Gripper
Install an MG90 servo into the gripper housing.
Connect the gripper linkage to the servo horn.

# Step 7: Route the Wiring

Route all servo wires neatly through the arm structure.

Recommended routing:

* Secure wires with zip ties.
* Leave enough slack at each joint for movement.
* Keep wires away from moving parts.

Servo assignments:

| Servo   | Function |
| ------- | -------- |
| Servo 0 | Base     |
| Servo 1 | Shoulder |
| Servo 2 | Elbow    |
| Servo 3 | Wrist    |
| Servo 4 | Gripper  |

---

# Step 8: Connect Servos to the Servo Driver

Connect each servo to the servo driver module.

| Driver Channel | Servo    |
| -------------- | -------- |
| CH0            | Base     |
| CH1            | Shoulder |
| CH2            | Elbow    |
| CH3            | Wrist    |
| CH4            | Gripper  |

Verify servo polarity:

* Brown/Black = GND
* Red = +5V
* Orange/Yellow = Signal

---

# Step 9: Connect Servo Driver to Arduino Uno

Connect the servo driver module to the Arduino Uno.

| Servo Driver | Arduino Uno |
| ------------ | ----------- |
| VCC          | 5V          |
| GND          | GND         |
| SDA          | A4          |
| SCL          | A5          |

---

# Step 10: Connect Power Supply

1. Connect the 5V 2A power supply to the servo driver's external power input.
2. Double-check polarity before powering the system.
3. Ensure all connections are secure.

**Important:** Power the servos from the external 5V supply, not directly from the Arduino.

---

# Operating Instructions

## Power-Up Procedure

1. Verify all wiring connections.
2. Plug the 5V 2A power supply into the servo driver module.
3. Connect the Arduino Uno to the PC using the USB cable.
4. Wait for the Arduino to be detected by the computer.

## Running the Software

1. Open the project folder on your computer.
2. Launch the Python control application.
3. Select the Arduino COM port from the software.
4. Click Connect.
5. Wait for the connection confirmation message.
6. Use the control interface to move:

   * Base
   * Shoulder
   * Elbow
   * Wrist
   * Gripper

